beast2 voice interface draft 1






beast2 voice interface draft 1

name  
    beast2 voice interface

purpose  
    provide a fast, low-friction voice layer for interacting with blue2 and beast2 systems  
    convert spoken intent into structured, traceable actions  
    maintain stability, determinism, and user control

---

principles  

    no automatic compute  
    user intent starts all actions  

    short input  
    short output  

    interruptible at all times  

    append-only logs  
    no hidden state mutation  

    voice is convenience layer  
    not source of truth  

    all important outputs become artifacts  

---

interaction model  

    tap  
    → speak  
    → parse  
    → confirm (implicit or explicit)  
    → execute  
    → return result  

    loop:

        speak  
        → act  
        → observe  
        → adjust  

---

core commands (v1 minimal)  

    save this  
    define this  
    summarize this  
    find this  
    log this  

    move up  
    move down  
    move left  
    move right  

    open  
    close  

    stop  

---

command grammar  

    structure:

        verb + object + modifier

    examples:

        save this as artifact  
        define drift  
        summarize last note  
        move up small  
        find taco definition  

---

parsing rules  

    convert speech → structured command  

    example:

        "move up a little bit"
        →
        action: move  
        axis: up  
        amount: small  

    rules:

        tolerate noise  
        normalize synonyms  
        reject ambiguous commands or mark as #maybe  

---

execution model  

    voice command  
    → parsed command  
    → safety check  
    → execution  
    → result artifact  

    no command executes without passing:

        validation  
        bounds check (if physical)  
        format check (if data)

---

feedback model  

    output must be:

        short  
        clear  
        stateful  

    examples:

        saved  
        definition stored  
        moving up  
        target not found  

    optional expansion on request:

        explain  
        show details  

---

camera / sensor integration  

    sensors produce facts, not raw data  

    example:

        red object at center: no  
        distance: medium  
        grip: open  

    blue2 operates on facts, not pixels  

---

state and logging  

    all actions logged:

        #log  
        command  
        result  
        timestamp  

    artifacts stored separately:

        #artifact  
        content  
        source  

    no silent actions  

---

error handling  

    unclear input:

        ask for clarification  
        or mark as #maybe  

    unsafe command:

        reject  
        explain briefly  

    failed execution:

        report  
        allow retry  

---

safety  

    physical systems:

        enforce bounds  
        limit speed  
        step-based movement only  

    data systems:

        no overwrite without explicit intent  
        preserve prior versions  

---

voice ux rules  

    fast start (<300ms ideal)  
    low latency response  

    allow interruption mid-response  

    avoid long speech output  

    default to concise responses  

---

blue2 role  

    interpret intent  
    suggest actions  
    store artifacts  
    assist reasoning  

    not autonomous  

---

boundaries  

    voice layer:

        input + output only  

    core system:

        logic  
        storage  
        execution  

---

future extensions  

    multi-step commands  
    context chaining  
    personalization  

    bee integration:

        quick yes/no validation before execution  

---

philosophy  

    voice is not magic  
    voice is a handle  

    system must remain:

        inspectable  
        predictable  
        controllable  

